com.intel.icecp.module.fork

Class ForkModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.icecp.module.fork.ForkModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.intel.icecp.core.Module

    @ModuleProperty(name="ForkModule",
                attributes={IncomingChannelAttribute.class,MessageFilterAttribute.class,ForkedChannelsAttribute.class})
public class ForkModule
extends Object
implements com.intel.icecp.core.Module

    Fork module that shall fork an incoming channel into multiple channels based on MessageFilterAttribute in the incoming message. It shall take an incoming channel URI as configuration and exposes a IncomingChannelAttribute attribute and expose resulting channels (channel URIs) externally through the ForkedChannelsAttribute attribute. The forked channels are of the format <incomingChannel URI>/<extracted value from the messageFilter>

    Ex: If the messageFilter is $.sensoridentifier and incomingChannel is ndn:/test-fork/ and the incoming message looked like: {"timestamp":..., "sensoridentifier":"sensorId1234"} The resulting forked channel will have the format ndn:/test-fork/sensorId1234
